Description: Fragment from lower body of East Greek (South Ionian) Middle Wild Goat Style II pottery oinochoe; brown-grey clay with black and white line inclusions and silver mica (Munsell 5YT 6/4 - 5/1); exterior: cream slip, dark brown and red paint; from left, part of a grazing wild goat to right (head, neck and foreleg preserved) and hindquarters of a second wild goat to right; filling ornaments: lozenges, swastikas; red patch on haunch of one of the wild goats. Overfired.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.042)
Schlotzhauer 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus Naukratis (p. 93-4, Nau 37, pl. 8i)
